      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "An equivalency matrix documents the correspondence between experimental test parameters and simulation input parameters for all boundary conditions. Differences between test and simulation conditions (e.g. use of bovine synovial substitute vs. human synovial fluid) are quantified and their impact on QoIs assessed via sensitivity analysis. The viscosity difference (< 8% at the operating temperature) is shown to produce < 5% change in deposition fraction. Achieved level 2 meets the MRL 3 requirement.",
