  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-decision",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors have been assessed and all achieved levels meet or exceed the required levels for Model Risk Level 3. The velocity field validation (MAE 4.2%) and particle deposition fraction validation (within 15% across three gait conditions) both satisfy the defined acceptance criteria. The GCI study confirms discretization errors are negligible relative to model-form and input uncertainties. Sensitivity analysis identifies particle diameter and synovial fluid viscosity as dominant uncertainty sources; both have been characterised experimentally and their uncertainties propagated through Monte Carlo analysis. The 95% prediction intervals bracket all experimental measurements. The simulation protocol has been demonstrated reproducible by an independent analyst. The model is accepted for use in predicting relative wear-debris particle distribution patterns for the Class II TKR implant within the defined operating envelope.",
